mdnsd (1.0) stable; urgency=medium

  * Full IPv6 support: mdnsd and mquery now query and answer over the
    ff02::fb group, not just advertise AAAA records over IPv4 (issue #10)
  * Support multiple IPv4/IPv6 addresses per interface, with all of a
    host's services sharing one host name, by Thom Nichols, VoltServer
    (issue #77)
  * Track interface and address changes in real time over netlink,
    instead of polling, on Linux
  * mquery: add device discovery mode (-D/-d/-T)
  * RFC 6763 compliance: the service PTR now points at the service
    instance, and responses carry the matching SRV, TXT, and address
    records in the additional section (issues #76, #80)
  * Keep key-only TXT attributes (boolean flags) instead of dropping
    them (issue #58)
  * Resolve .local names on the host with libnss-mdns; the mdnsd package
    now Recommends it (issue #19)
  * libmdnsd: installed headers no longer pull in the build's config.h,
    so programs can build against the library again (issue #75)
  * Send goodbye packets when an interface is removed, by Gavin J
    (issue #91)
  * Unify the shell and unit tests under one Automake harness (issue #66)
  * Fix #37: _lmatch() read one byte past the root label
  * Fix #79: mquery sent malformed packets when known-answer suppression
    kicked in
  * Fix #84: use-after-free of a freed record in uanswers
  * Fix #92: use-after-free in mdnsd_set_interface_addresses
  * Fix #82: conflict detection now considers all of an interface's
    addresses, by Thom Nichols, VoltServer
  * Fix a one-byte over-read in txt2sd(), and a memory overflow
  * Library SONAME bumped to libmdnsd.so.2, so the runtime package is
    now libmdnsd2 (was libmdnsd1)
  * Packaging: debhelper compat 13, Standards-Version 4.6.2.0

 -- Joachim Wiberg <troglobit@gmail.com>  Thu, 25 Jun 2026 12:00:00 +0200

mdnsd (0.12) stable; urgency=medium

  * libmdnsd, mquery, and mdnsd: add support for IPv6 AAAA records,
    including display in mquery, by Florian Zschocke, devolo AG
  * mdnsd: add -H hostname support, for testing purposes mainly
  * mquery: add -l debug support
  * mquery: display every answer received when in mdns-scan mode
  * Initial support for a test framework, including cmocka unit tests
  * Add support for disabling installation of man pages
  * Add support for building without mquery
  * Fix #11: port to other UNIX systems (FreeBSD, NetBSD, OpenBSD,
    DragonFly BSD, and illumos/SmartOS)
  * Fix #49: various typos in log messages
  * Fix #52: double free, introduced in v0.11
  * Fix #55: mDNS conflict check, by Florian Zschocke, devolo AG
  * Fix #56: parse A records keeping network byte order, by Florian
    Zschocke, devolo AG
  * Fix #65: make SPRIME actually a prime number, by Florian Zschocke,
    devolo AG
  * Fix #74: segfault when the mdnsd interface is removed

 -- Joachim Wiberg <troglobit@gmail.com>  Sun, 22 Jan 2023 12:00:00 +0100

mdnsd (0.11) stable; urgency=medium

  * Add support for multiple interfaces, similar to running one
    mdnsd v0.10 per interface, sharing the same .conf files, issue #8
  * Removed `-a ADDR` flag, not applicable anymore
  * The `-i IFACE` option now limits mdnsd to run on one interface
  * Add support for query type ANY, by Peter Fleer, issue #34
  * Create PID file when starting up, and touch on .conf reload.  This
    is used by process supervisors like Finit to acknowledge that the
    process (mdnsd) is done and ready to serve requests again
  * Updated mquery tool to behave a bit more like mdns-scan(1), except
    with more command line options.  mquery still only runs on one
    interface, unlike mdnsd itself
  * Fix #33: multiple code cleanups and minor fixes by Wolfgang Rösler
  * Fix #35: validate port number in .conf file
  * Fix #38: possible NULL pointer dereference and memory leaks when
    reading .conf files, by Wolfgang Rösler
  * Fix #39: multiple fixes by Peter Fleer
  * Fix conflict detection
  * If a conflict is detected, append `-index` suffix to hostname
    to uniqify the name -- this happens in multi-deploy scenarios
  * When reloading .conf files, delete previously published records
  * Drop own, looped back, multicast packets -- only if we detect
    it as our own published records
  * Send publish records only if probes have gone unanswered
  * Fix #43: _ldecomp() breaking on long name offsets, by Chris Beaumont

 -- Joachim Wiberg <troglobit@gmail.com>  Tue, 04 Jan 2022 20:45:00 +0200

mdnsd (0.10) stable; urgency=medium

  * Add mdnsd.service.5 for service record files
  * Memory leak fixes
  * Append text field to the TXT record instead of the A record, in the
    case of a PTR type, the name must also match
  * Fix potential endless loop when decoding message labels
  * Skip message processing when the packet parser failed
  * Misc. fuzzer fixes

